The utility says it’s taken the decision after protest action in the area. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says it’s had to suspend operations in Ga-Rankuwa for safety reasons. The utility says it’s taken the decision after protest action in the area. Community members have blocked the roads with rocks and burning tires after Eskom removed their illegal connections. The power utility started the power cuts on Wednesday. Eskom technicians are on standby for any emergencies amid the protest. Eskom's Daphne Mokwena explained: “Our security guards informed us the area is unsafe to get into. We deployed staff elsewhere.”